cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.CV, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a novel feature selection algorithm that is based on Gradient Boosted Trees, which is a popular machine learning technique used in several sub-fields of computer science. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also evaluates the proposed algorithm on several real-world datasets, which suggests that it could be relevant to the sub-categories cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
